# Metrics Glossary

## Production Metrics (from daily_scrape_data)

| Metric | Formula | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Contact Rate | `(answered_calls / total_calls) * 100` | % of dials that were answered |
| Close Rate | `(apps / answered_calls) * 100` | % of answered calls that became apps |
| Dial Yield | `apps / total_calls` | Raw efficiency: apps per dial |
| Talk Time | Cumulative seconds on calls | Display as MM:SS |

## Leads Pool Metrics (from leads_pool_daily_data)

| Metric | Formula | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Pool Efficiency | `pool_talk_time_min / pool_dials` | Minutes per dial — key gaming indicator |
| Assign Rate | `self_assigned_leads / answered_calls × 100` | % of answered calls the agent self-assigned as leads |
| Gaming Flag | Based on Pool Efficiency thresholds | See below |

### Assign Rate Thresholds

All pool leads are unassigned. Agents should self-assign every answered contact — including
not interested and DNC — to remove leads from rotation and prevent unnecessary repeat calls.

| Assign Rate | Interpretation |
|---|---|
| >= 65% | Healthy — properly managing pool contacts and cleaning rotation |
| 45–64% | Below target — leaving contacted leads in pool to get called again |
| < 45% | Cherry-picking — only assigning interested leads, ignoring DNC/not interested |

### Pool Efficiency Thresholds

| Efficiency | Interpretation |
|---|---|
| > 1 min/dial | Too slow — distracted, over-noting, idle time |
| 0.5–1 min/dial | Healthy, realistic workflow |
| 0.3–0.5 min/dial | Fast but acceptable |
| < 0.3 min/dial | Likely gaming / rapid skipping |

## Pipeline Metrics (from pipeline_compliance_daily)

| Metric | Formula | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Total Stale | `past_due + new_leads + (call_queue * staleRate)` | staleRate: T1=15%, T2=10%, T3=8% |
| Revenue at Risk | `total_stale * avgPremium` | Uses agent's 30-day rolling avg premium (falls back to tier avg) |
| Projected Recovery | `total_stale * closeRate * avgPremium` | Uses agent's 30-day rolling close rate (falls back to tier avg) |
| Pipeline Health Score | Composite of 4 sub-scores (0-25 each) | See pipelineIntelligence.ts |
| Past Due Delta (d/d) | `today_past_due - yesterday_past_due` | Negative = improving, positive = deteriorating |

### Revenue Model Data Sources

Agent-level stats require minimum 3 days of data and 2+ sales (premium) or 5+ leads (close rate).
Below threshold, falls back to tier-level averages computed from same 30-day window.
Fallback constants when no data: T1=$400/8%, T2=$300/6%, T3=$250/4%.

## Follow-Up Compliance

| Metric | Formula | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| F/U Compliance % | `(1 - pastDue / (pastDue + todaysFollowUps)) * 100` | Point-in-time ratio |
| Past Due Delta | `today.pastDue - prior_day.pastDue` | d/d trend indicator |

If both pastDue and todaysFollowUps are 0, compliance = 100% (clean pipeline or no assignments).
The delta is the more actionable signal — a rising past-due count regardless of ratio means deterioration.

## Agent Performance Funnel (from agent_performance_daily)

| Metric | Definition | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Dials | Total outbound dials | Self-explanatory |
| Leads Worked | Unique leads agent worked in the period | Each lead counts once per agent |
| Contact Made | Leads that hit "contact made" status as first occurrence | CRM status change, not just call answered |
| Conversations | Calls between 2 min and < 15 min | Duration bucket — mutually exclusive with Presentations |
| Presentations | Calls 15 min or more | Duration bucket — mutually exclusive with Conversations |
| Follow Up (Appt Set) | Follow-up appointments set | Self-explanatory |
| Sale Made | Sales closed | Self-explanatory |
| Talk Min | Total talk time in minutes | Self-explanatory |

### Funnel Conversion Rates

| Rate | Formula | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Contact % | `contactsMade / leadsWorked × 100` | What % of worked leads were meaningfully contacted |
| Contact to Close % | `sales / contactsMade × 100` | Overall sales efficiency from contact |
| Conversation to Close % | `sales / conversations × 100` | Close rate from 2-15 min calls |
| Presentation to Close % | `sales / presentations × 100` | Close rate from 15+ min calls |

**Critical**: Conversations and Presentations are **parallel duration buckets**, NOT sequential funnel stages.
A call is either a Conversation (2-15 min) OR a Presentation (15+ min), never both.
All close % rates are calculated as `sales / [stage]`, not stage-to-stage.

## Contact Rate vs Connect Rate vs Contact %

- **Contact Rate** = production dials answered (daily_scrape_data)
- **Connect Rate** = pool leads meaningfully contacted (leads_pool_daily_data)
- **Contact %** = leads that hit contact-made status / leads worked (agent_performance_daily)
- These are three distinct metrics from three different reports — never conflate them
